    "body": "### Problem\n\nHi,\n\nOpenBSD packager here.\n\nFor the last few releases, the tar tests have been failing on OpenBSD:\n```\n        From test_plugin_tar.vim:                                                                                                                                │ePresets.json cmake\n        Found errors in Test_tar_basic():                                                                                                                        │          deps.txt\n        command line..script /usr/local/pobj/neovim-0.12.2/neovim-0.12.2/test/old/testdir/runtest.vim[659]..function RunTheTest[61]..Test_tar_basic line 1       │arrakis:cmake.deps> rg\n1: Pattern 'testtar/' does not match 'testtar'                                                                                                                   │ 1.52.1-0\n        Found errors in Test_tar_evil():                                                                                                                         │\n        command line..script /usr/local/pobj/neovim-0.12.2/neovim-0.12.2/test/old/testdir/runtest.vim[659]..function RunTheTest[61]..Test_tar_evil line 15       │\n: Pattern '/etc/ax-pwn' does not match 'etc/ax-pwn'                                                                                                              │arrakis:cmake.deps> rg\n        Caught exception in Test_tar_evil(): Vim(read):E484: Can't open file etc/ax-pwn @ command line..script /usr/local/pobj/neovim-0.12.2/neovim-0.12.2       │ fbb36bb6bfa88716a47c5\n/test/old/testdir/runtest.vim[659]..function RunTheTest[61]..Test_tar_evil[25]..<SNR>10_TarBrowseSelect[27]..tar#Read, line 114                                  │8bcf9ce9f2ef752abac\n        Found errors in Test_tar_path_traversal_with_nowrapscan():                                                                                               │arrakis:cmake.deps> rg\n        command line..script /usr/local/pobj/neovim-0.12.2/neovim-0.12.2/test/old/testdir/runtest.vim[659]..function RunTheTest[61]..Test_tar_path_travers       │ fbb36bb6bfa88716a47c5\nal_with_nowrapscan[2]..<SNR>8_CopyFile line 2: Can't copy samples/evil.tar                                                                                       │8bcf9ce9f2ef752abac\n        command line..script /usr/local/pobj/neovim-0.12.2/neovim-0.12.2/test/old/testdir/runtest.vim[659]..function RunTheTest[61]..Test_tar_path_travers       │arrakis:cmake.deps> ls\nal_with_nowrapscan line 15: Pattern '/etc/ax-pwn' does not match 'etc/ax-pwn'\n```\n\n^ This was with neovim-0.12.2 release.\n\nSorry, I haven't had time to investigate further.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nrun the old test suite.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ntests pass\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nneovim-0.12.2 release\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nOpenBSD-current/amd64\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nn/a\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nn/a\n\n### Installation\n\nOpenBSD package",
